      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "My final input is to ensure the standardized protocol explicitly retains the ability to flag *pattern-based* systemic issues, irrespective of initial location scoring. A raw application of standardized metrics might treat large-scale, non-visible issues (like structural safety lapses in overcrowded areas) as merely minor deviations. I recommend building in a meta-layer that flags deviations from *expected operational norms* across all regions, rather than just against target thresholds.",
      "source": "target",
